Ford Motor Company, established in 1903, holds a significant place in automotive history 
as an iconic American automaker. From the revolutionary Model T to the modern F-Series trucks, 
Ford has been synonymous with innovation and mass production, making cars accessible to 
the masses. The company's lineup includes a range of vehicles such as the versatile Ford 
Escape, the rugged Ford Explorer, and the performance-oriented Mustang. Ford's commitment
to sustainability is evident in its electrification efforts, highlighted by the Mustang 
Mach-E electric SUV. With a legacy of innovation, Ford continues to evolve, integrating
cutting-edge technology while staying true to its heritage of building vehicles that 
resonate with a diverse global audience.